---

## Directory Purposes

### 1. `sales-docs/` — Public & Website-Safe

| Attribute | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| **Audience** | Potential clients, website visitors, sales team |
| **Tone** | Executive, confident, trust-building |
| **Contains** | Value propositions, features, security overview |
| **Never Contains** | Code, credentials, internal architecture, pricing internals |
| **Shareable** | Yes — website, PDF, demos |

**Files to Include:**

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `Product_Overview.md` | High-level what SecureChat is and does |
| `Key_Features.md` | Feature list with business benefits |
| `Security_at_a_Glance.md` | End-to-end encryption, compliance, privacy (conceptual) |
| `Scalability_and_Reliability.md` | Enterprise-grade, uptime, architecture highlights |
| `Industries_and_Use_Cases.md` | Healthcare, finance, legal, enterprises |
| `Why_Choose_SecureChat.md` | Differentiators, comparison points |
| `Pricing_Tiers.md` | Starter, Business, Enterprise tiers (if applicable) |
| `FAQ_for_Buyers.md` | Common pre-sale questions |

---

### 2. `client-docs/` — Post-Purchase Functional Docs

| Attribute | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| **Audience** | Paying clients, their admins, end-users |
| **Tone** | Helpful, instructional, professional |
| **Contains** | How-to guides, feature explanations, admin controls |
| **Never Contains** | Internal code, secrets, infrastructure details |
| **Shareable** | Yes — to paying clients only |

**Files to Include:**

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `Getting_Started.md` | First steps after purchase |
| `User_Guide.md` | How end-users use the app |
| `Admin_Guide.md` | Admin panel, user management, settings |
| `Feature_Reference/` | Detailed feature usage (one file per feature) |
| `Deployment_Overview.md` | High-level deployment expectations |
| `Maintenance_and_Support.md` | How updates work, support channels |
| `Troubleshooting.md` | Common issues and solutions |

**Cross-Reference Rule:**
> For feature lists, reference `../sales-docs/Key_Features.md` instead of repeating.

---

### 3. `developer-docs/` — Technical Implementation

| Attribute | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| **Audience** | Developers, engineers, DevOps |
| **Tone** | Technical, precise, actionable |
| **Contains** | Setup, architecture, APIs, deployment |
| **Never Contains** | Interview answers, sales language |
| **Shareable** | Internal team only |

**Subdirectory Structure:**

| Directory | Purpose | Files |
|-----------|---------|-------|
| `setup/` | Getting development running | Quick_Start, Environment, Docker, Git |
| `architecture/` | System design | Architecture, Database, Socket Events |
| `backend/` | API and server | APIs, Auth Flow, Services |
| `mobile/` | React Native | Setup, Components, State |
| `devops/` | Deployment & operations | DevOps Story, Deploy Guide, Monitoring |
| `security/` | Encryption implementation | E2E Encryption technical details |

**Anti-Repetition Rules:**
1. Database schema appears ONLY in `architecture/Database_Schema.md`
2. API endpoints appear ONLY in `backend/API_Reference.md`
3. Docker commands appear ONLY in `setup/Docker_Setup.md`
4. Other files reference these instead of repeating

---

### 4. `interview-prep/` — Personal Interview Preparation

| Attribute | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| **Audience** | You only |
| **Tone** | Conversational, Q&A format |
| **Contains** | Stories, trade-offs, lessons, interview answers |
| **Never Contains** | Raw technical docs (reference developer-docs instead) |
| **Shareable** | Never |

**Existing Files (Already Organized):**
- [01_Project_Story.md](file:///media/swastik/focus/projects%202026/chat%20app/0.0/documents/Interview/SecureChat/01_Project_Story.md) → "Tell me about a project"
